<table border="0" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="1" bgcolor="#000000" width="100%"><tr>
<td bgcolor="#CACACA" align="left">
<font size="3" color="#363636"><b>News: Legends of Knights Initiative</b></font>
<br><font color="#999999" size="1">Posted by <a href="http://www.knightsinitiative.com">webmaster</a> on Saturday, January 04 @ 23:19:08 EST  (10 reads)</font>
<br><b>Topic</b> <a href="search.php?query=&amp;topic=1&amp;author=">news and updates</a>
</td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
<font color="#999999"><b><a href="search.php?query=&amp;topic=1"><img src="images/topics/kilogo.gif" border="0" Alt="news and updates" align="right" hspace="10" vspace="10"></a></B></font>
<font size="2" color="#505050"><br>
Well we're here!  Legends of Knights Initiative (or as we like to nickname it LoKI) is all ready to go.  We have our guild tagged, and have a bunch of new members, as well many of our old friends who have returned.<br>
<br>
Guriab and I are co-leading.  This means that he and I have the same amount of access and control over guild functions.  This unique way of handing guild administration will definately help, as well as provide a means of checks and balances.  For example, I will have guild leader controls in January, and in February, I will be transferring them to Guriab, and we will rotate back and forth like that on a montly (give or take a few days) basis.<br>
<br>
I would like to make this guild as little involved with control, rules, and politics as possible.  With that said anyone is allowed to join our guild, and anyone who has reached level 20 or more with us is free to ask to become an officer and help out.  Our rules is in our charter, which are mostly common sense.  I'd like to keep the rules as basic as that, and only change them if there's a need to do it.<br>
<br>
An officer's duty is to help out a little more than what's expected, and set an example for others.  I know Curisz has offered to have one of his characters volunteer to lead raids, which will be very nice of him when the time comes.  Other things I'd like are special LoKI events and guild picnics (with of course prizes and contests).<br>
<br>
Here's who we have so far for officers:<br>
<br>
Leaders:<br>
Ariza (Sumadi)<br>
Guriab<br>
<br>
Officers:<br>
Goheal (Gilama)<br>
Nytcretur<br>
-looking to add more<br>
<br>
Members:<br>
-please sign up on this website so I can add you to the member roster<br>
<br>
<br>
Guriab and I are going to try to make this guild as fun as possible, and I am glad that we are still KI, even though we are a Legend in the making =)<br>
<br>
-Ariza (Sumadi)<br>
<br>
PS: please send me a tell (to Ariza or Guriab) in the game if you are a KI alumni and would like to be guild tagged (all alumni are automatic officers).  Also you may email me at webmaster@knightsinitiative.com and I will look for your character online next time i'm on :)<br></font>
</td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#ffffff" align="right">
<font size="2">(<a href="article.php?sid=94">comments?</a>)</font>
